A [[wee dram]] is a [[Scottish]] euphemism  for a shot of [[Scotch Whisky]] -- hopefully a [[Single Malt Whisky]], from the fragrant far north-east coast [[distillery]] of [[Glenmorangie]] or the peaty south west-coast [[Laphroaig]] but more likely a central belt [[Whisky blend]] like [[Famous Grouse]]. Given to guests and visitors, it is a typically [[Scottish]] gesture of hospitality, camaderie and National pride.